p.01703376c4a81c0e9d91: Transform a Cloud Object to JSON
p.01703376c4a81c0e9d92:
Transform an instance of a Cloud Object or list of instances to JSON.

The properties of the related business model are used as properties of the json.

**Example**:
```
CloudObjectToJSON(`GPS Coordinate` object) -> { "Latitude":15, "Longitude": 25," name": "GPS Coordinate" }

CloudObjectToJSON(`List of GPS Coordinate` objects) -> [ { "Latitude":15, "Longitude": 25, "name": "GPS Coordinate"}, { "Latitude": 13, "Longitude": 22, " name" : "GPS Coordinate" } ] 

```
Instance of Cloud Object or List
JSON object or array of objects
Triggered if provided source is not a correct Cloud Object of List of Cloud Objects
If true will only serialize the properties of the objects, otherwise will includes the related objects
